role: dev
task: S04-T2
title: Command-center typography and hierarchy
gate: OPEN
stack_source: @incoming/requirements.md
stack: [TypeScript, React, MobX, Material UI]
requires: [UI]

objective: |
  Establish a technological, military-grade typographic system: data-dense readability,
  clear hierarchy (mission-critical → secondary), and "generals WOW" at a glance.

context:
  - Command-center UIs favor monospace or technical display fonts for data; clear headings for hierarchy.
  - High contrast and consistent scale support quick scanning.

steps:
  1. Define or adopt a type scale (e.g. --font-mono, --font-display) for data and labels.
  2. Apply mono/display to status values, IDs, timestamps; reserve readable sans for headings and body.
  3. Enforce hierarchy: primary info (size/weight) > secondary > tertiary; avoid visual noise.
  4. Ensure line-height and letter-spacing meet readability under dark theme (S02/S03 contrast).

acceptance-criteria:
  - Typography tokens documented and used consistently.
  - Data-dense blocks remain scannable; headings clearly separate sections.
  - Contrast and legibility validated against existing dark theme.
